---
name: the_fold
description: Teach and maintain the Herald fold teach view and its supporting modules.
compatibility: Sixth AI
allowed-tools: read_file, read_batch, list_files, search_files, execute_command
---

Purpose

Use this skill when you need to work on the Herald teach view located at `../herald/teach/views/the_fold/index.ts`.

When to Use

- When the fold teach view or its helper modules need review.
- When you need to trace how fold content is assembled.
- When a task references the fold lesson, lesson data, or rendering logic.

Workflow

1. Read `../herald/teach/views/the_fold/index.ts`.
2. Read any sibling helpers or child modules such as `../herald/teach/views/the_fold/_helpers.ts`.
3. Follow imports to any local modules that shape the view output.
4. Make the smallest change needed and keep the view semantics intact.
5. Verify that any related content or copy still matches the teach intent.

Guardrails

- Do not edit unrelated teach views.
- Do not rename the view folder or exported identifiers unless the task explicitly requires it.
- Preserve the local data shape and formatting conventions used by the view.

Output

- Report the files reviewed and the helper modules consulted.
- Summarize any edits made to the view or its supporting modules.